cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks such as text generation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes metrics to evaluate the performance of text generation models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as NLP is a subfield of AI. The paper also proposes the use of a deep learning model called BERT, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it proposes a feature-based measure that uses a deep model to evaluate the performance of text generation models.
